<span id="freeTextContainer17087716090391541893">I was not particularly touched by the story told by the three voices of this novel, but I was not indifferent to the author&apos;s pen either.<br/>A strange feeling, mixed then.<br/>In a remote village, once a prosperous banana plantation, a death by suicide awaits his burial. However, the tenacious contempt of the villagers for the deceased is delaying events.<br/>Yet a man is keen to honour the promise made to his old friend in the past. Her daughter and grandson are also present, watch, wait, tell ...<br/>Loneliness,</span>
  <span id="freeText17087716090391541893" style="display:none">I was not particularly touched by the story told by the three voices of this novel, but I was not indifferent to the author's pen either.<br />A strange feeling, mixed then.<br />In a remote village, once a prosperous banana plantation, a death by suicide awaits his burial. However, the tenacious contempt of the villagers for the deceased is delaying events.<br />Yet a man is keen to honour the promise made to his old friend in the past. Her daughter and grandson are also present, watch, wait, tell ...<br />Loneliness, abandonment, doubt and resentment are at the heart of a choral tale with a haunting rhythm, but not monotonous and sometimes poetic.<br />With smells and shadows mingle the tension of expectation and the echo of memories.</span>
