<span id="freeTextContainer14945250301841003879">Another good tale from Marquez. This is now my sixth book of his, so it&apos;s safe to say he is one of my favourite writers. It&apos;s within <i>Leaf Storm</i> that he first wrote of Macondo, the fictional village in which his famous novel <i>One Hundred Years of Solitude</i> is set, published twelve years later; and a familiar name crops up once or twice, too. It&apos;s possible to see faint traces of Marquez&apos;s later themes here too, solitude itself being an important one.<br/><br/>The halfway point in my challenge, 35/70, hit just</span>
  <span id="freeText14945250301841003879" style="display:none">Another good tale from Marquez. This is now my sixth book of his, so it's safe to say he is one of my favourite writers. It's within <i>Leaf Storm</i> that he first wrote of Macondo, the fictional village in which his famous novel <i>One Hundred Years of Solitude</i> is set, published twelve years later; and a familiar name crops up once or twice, too. It's possible to see faint traces of Marquez's later themes here too, solitude itself being an important one.<br /><br />The halfway point in my challenge, 35/70, hit just in time too, on the last day of June (woo!)</span>
